{"type":"finding","iteration":8,"id":"S1-08A-write-if-changed-wrapper","dimension":"D1","focus":"S1-08","summary":"loop-cli-main suppresses redundant daemon writes with an in-memory lastSerialized map: persist builds LoopMeta, JSON.stringify compares against the cached string, returns early when equal, and calls saveLoop only on change.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:23",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:263",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:279",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:281",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:285"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","supportFiles":[".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/atomic-state.vitest.ts"],"portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Adds a shared no-op-on-identical snapshot primitive so reducers and merge scripts avoid duplicate full-state rewrites and mtime churn."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":8,"id":"S1-08B-whole-snapshot-upsert-boundary","dimension":"D1","focus":"S1-08","summary":"state.ts is the full-array persistence sink: it reads JSON arrays, falls back to an empty array on invalid state, upserts a LoopMeta by id, and writes the pretty-serialized whole array. The diff gate stays outside that domain-specific upsert path.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/state.ts:29",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/state.ts:40",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/state.ts:87",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/state.ts:92",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:279"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Lets our registry, dashboard, and merged-state writers remain simple full-snapshot writers while centralizing identical-snapshot suppression."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":8,"id":"S1-08C-cache-lifecycle-coverage","dimension":"D1","focus":"S1-08","summary":"The reference cache is ephemeral and per loop: deletion clears lastSerialized, but init does not seed it from disk, so the first persist after process restart writes and subsequent identical persists no-op.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:38",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:238",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:281"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/atomic-state.vitest.ts","portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Adds regression coverage for repeat no-op writes, first write after empty cache, and explicit invalidation semantics before adopting the helper."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":8,"id":"S1-08D-preserve-fsync-durability","dimension":"D1","focus":"S1-08","summary":"loop-cli-main's atomic writer is temp-file plus rename, while our atomic-state writer already fsyncs the temp file and attempts to fsync the parent directory. Porting should add the diff gate without downgrading our durability contract.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/shared/fs-utils.ts:9",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/shared/fs-utils.ts:12",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts:58",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts:63",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts:66"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win","whyItHelps":"Reduces write amplification while keeping deep-loop-runtime crash-safety stronger than the reference implementation."}
{"type":"observation","iteration":8,"id":"S1-08-premise-correction","summary":"The focus prompt named daemon/state.ts as the serialize-diff implementation, but in this snapshot state.ts only persists full arrays; daemon/manager.ts owns the actual serialized-snapshot comparison.","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/state.ts:40",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts:279"]}
